C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Πι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Πι\">Πι̣\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τέκτων\">τέκτων\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"κάλλιστόν\">κάλ̣[λιστόν]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ποτε\">ποτε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῦτον\">τοῦτον\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἀνεῖ\n                    λε\">[ἀ]νεῖ-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>λε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"κίων\">κίων\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Μοῖρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μοῖρα\">Μοῖρα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ὃς\">ὃς\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"κατέλειψε\">κατέλειψε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"πατρὶ\">πατρὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"λύπην\">λύπην\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"δεινοτάτην\">δεινοτάτην\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al8-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">8\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησε\">ἔζησε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\">ἔτη\u003C/span> κ̣β´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":126,"date":3,"citedRange":234,"ptr":235,"ref":236,"title":2,"citation":4},"94 no. 2 fig. 2",{"target":129},{"_":131,"target":131},{"file":238,"uri":238,"title":239,"status":240,"editionAuthor":11,"type":242,"objectType":246,"material":247,"condition":248,"layoutDesc":250,"handNote":255,"date":403,"places":407,"geo":410,"country":71,"region":72,"settlement":412,"repository":413,"idno":416,"textLang":418,"facsimile":420,"provenance":60,"letterHeights":423,"publications":424,"zotero":427,"keywords":430,"html":436,"bibl":437},"ISic002945","A gymnasiarch crowns a group of youths",{"_":241},"edited",{"_":243,"ana":244,"ref":245},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"ana":249},"#condition.fragment",{"layout":251},{"p":252,"rs":253,"damage":254},"15 neatly carved lines of Greek letters, of which the first four are larger. There appears to be a slight vacat at the top; lines 1-3 are indented by the equivalent of 1-2 characters at most; from line 4 onwards the left indentation increases, with clear vacats after lines 5 and 6, and a fixed left margin (c.7 cm vacat) from line 7 onwards; a vacat is consistently inserted between each name in the list from line 7 onwards.",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},{"ana":34},{"lettering":256,"dimensions":384},[257,258],"Elegant letters with minimal serifs/terminations visible on longer strokes (e.g. on tau, sigma and epsilon). Alpha has straight bar; beta has smaller upper loop, with the two loops connected without meeting the vertical; epsilon has shorter middle bar; theta is a full-size circle with a detached horizontal stroke at the centre; kappa has full length arms; mu has near vertical first and last strokes, with the middle strokes meeting a small way above the baseline; xsi is formed of vertical with three horizontals, the middle one of shorter length; omicron is full-size; pi has equal length vertical strokes; sigma has horizontal topo and bottom strokes; phi is ovoid, with vertical taller than other letters (14-15mm); omega full size, near circular, but open at the base. Traces of a secondary text include lunate epsilon (see commentary).",{"_":259,"ref":260},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n    